29/10/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan has sent two foreign policy officials to meet with advisers of the two US presidential candidates -- Democrat Barack Obama and Republican John McCain, local media reported on Tuesday (October 28th).
Ahmet Davutoglu, Erdogan's chief foreign policy adviser, and Suat Kiniklioglu, deputy chairman of parliament's foreign affairs committee, will convey Turkey's stance on a number of crucial foreign policy issues to both campaigns.
These include Turkey's wish for continued co-operation in fighting the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party and US support for Turkey's proposal to establish a Caucasus Stability and Co-operation Platform that would bring together Turkey, Armenia, Georgia, Azerbaijan and Russia.
The US presidential election is less than a week away.
(Hurriyet, NTV, HaberTurk - 28/10/08)
